<img id="83993832" style="position: absolute; top: 204px; left: 338px; width: 747px; height: 340px;" src="data:image/png;base64," /><div class="textelement" id="73311432" style="position: absolute; top: 906px; left: 8px; font-size: 30px; color: FFFFFFFF;"><a href="/papers/teo-taylor-poster.pdf">Poster</a></div><div class="textelement" id="04771524.5" style="position: absolute; top: 972px; left: 9px; font-size: 24px; color: FFFFFFFF;">While this project focussed on the performance aspect of Processing, future-proofing Processing was another<br>key motivation for doing this project. I found out during a discussion with the Processing devs that <br>compatibility was a high priority, so I started working on<br><a href="/processing_angle.md">implementing ANGLE in Processing</a> as part of the efforts to modernise Processing after this paper was completed.<br><br>Though I managed to implement a Vulkan layer to this project, this was purely used for conceptual purposes<br>and in reality, is incompatible with many Processing sketches. In addition, this paper found that the<br>excessive CPU-to-GPU communication was a bottleneck in many of the tests. In the future, I may work on a<br>new revision of a Vulkan layer in Processing, specifically designed to address the CPU-to-GPU performance <br>bottlenecks.<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br></div><div class="textelement" id="91664824" style="position: absolute; top: 839px; left: 8px; font-size: 30px; color: FFFFFFFF;"><a href="/papers/teo-taylor-dissertation.pdf">Paper - "Implementation of a Vulkan-based renderer in Processing"</a></div><div class="textelement" id="65928452" style="position: absolute; top: 563px; left: 11px; font-size: 24px; color: FFFFFFFF;">This project is part of my final year dissertation, in which I implement and benchmark Vulkan in the<br>Processing framework, and compare it against its OpenGL-based renderer. The results from these tests show <br>that the Vulkan renderer performs better than the OpenGL-based renderer.<br><br>In addition, I created a poster as part of the university's poster event, which you can find on this page too.<br></div><div class="textelement" id="67201728" style="position: absolute; top: 779px; left: 8px; font-size: 30px; color: FFFFFFFF;">Here's the links:</div>
